{"slug": "arcane", "root": "arcane", "category": "quality", "gloss": "hidden/secret magical knowledge", "definition": "Arcane means hidden, secret, known only to initiates — the adjective of esoteric knowledge. In Magic it was also, briefly, a literal spell type.", "history": "Latin *arcanus*, 'shut up, secret,' from *arca*, 'a chest, a box' — the arcane is what's locked in the box (the same *arca* behind *ark*). The word carries the whole idea of magic as guarded, boxed-up knowledge. Magic's Kamigawa block made *Arcane* a spell subtype, the spirit-magic that 'Splices,' turning the adjective into a mechanic.", "def_sources": [{"label": "Etymonline, s.v. arcane", "where": "Etymology reference"}], "is_keyword": false, "etymology": {"origin": "Latin arcanus ‘secret, shut up’, from arca ‘a chest, box’", "first": "1540s", "note": "The arcane is what’s locked in the box (arca) — the same root as ‘ark.’ MTG made ‘Arcane’ a literal spell-type.", "hook": "The secret in the box: arca → arcane → ark.", "lang": "Latin"}, "essay": null, "sources": ["Etymonline (Douglas Harper)", "Wiktionary", "classical lexica (Lewis & Short, LSJ, Bosworth–Toller)", "Ted's historical-magic DBs (WitchcraftStudiesDB, AgrippaDOP, MedievalMagicDB)"], "stats": {"flavor_total": 21, "oracle_total": 124, "in_flavor_cards": 21, "in_oracle_cards": 96, "name_match_count": 31, "by_variant": {"arcane": 140, "arcanum": 4, "arcana": 1}, "first_year": 1994, "colors": {"R": 32, "C": 11, "W": 22, "U": 53, "G": 20, "B": 19}, "by_year": {"1994": 1, "2001": 2, "2004": 31, "2005": 42, "2007": 2, "2008": 1, "2013": 7, "2015": 4, "2016": 1, "2017": 4, "2018": 6, "2019": 2, "2020": 3, "2021": 11, "2022": 8, "2023": 2, "2024": 8, "2025": 3, "2026": 5}}, "cards": [{"id": "f5e3c26c-c28c-455f-a682-2597e4b92d10", "name": "Arcane Laboratory", "set": "7ED", "set_name": "Seventh Edition", "released": "2001-04-11", "type_line": "Enchantment", "rarity": "uncommon", "colors": ["U"], "img_small": "https://cards.scryfall.io/small/fr